title: The Widget Tree
tags: Structure Widgets WidgetTree

[[Widgets|WidgetModules]] in TiddlyWiki build a DOM-like Tree Structure called the ''Widget Tree''

The Widget Tree starts with the ''root Widget'' that initializes on [[Startup|RootWidget and Rendering Startup]] (see $:/core/modules/startup.js and $:/core/modules/startup/rootwidget.js for reference)

The Tree Structure allows walking the Tree up and down accessing the parent Widget through `this.parentWidget` and accessing child widgets through `this.children[index]` or `this.parentWidget.children[index]`


* root widget
** first child widget
*** first child-widget's child widget
**** ...
*** /first child-widget's child widget
*** sibling widget to first child-widget's child widget
*** /sibling widget to first child-widget's child widget
** /first child widget
** sibling widget to first child widget
*** ...
** /sibling widget to first child widget
** ...
* /root widget

<<.tip "some widgets don't make child widgets. widgets that make child widgets call the `makeChildWidgets` method, see WidgetModules and $:/core/modules/widgets/widget.js for reference">>
